                            <comment id="13411496" author="gtully" created="Wed, 11 Jul 2012 13:42:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In that case, the default jdbc adapter should work when explicitly set.&lt;br/&gt;
Can you try&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;    &amp;lt;persistenceAdapter&amp;gt;
      &amp;lt;jdbcPersistenceAdapter&amp;gt;
        &amp;lt;adapter&amp;gt;
           &amp;lt;defaultJDBCAdapter /&amp;gt;
         &amp;lt;/adapter&amp;gt;
      &amp;lt;/jdbcPersistenceAdapter&amp;gt;
    &amp;lt;/persistenceAdapter&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13411592" author="fredt" created="Wed, 11 Jul 2012 14:46:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, cannot test as I don&apos;t use ActiveMQ. Reporting due to HSQLDB concerns. It should work if the CREATE TABLE defines the type as BLOB.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also noted the BytesJDBCAdaptor simply contains redundant redefinitions of setBinaryData and getBinaryData methods in the superclass.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13821530" author="davsclaus" created="Wed, 13 Nov 2013 17:04:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah according the hsqldb data type guides we should use BLOB&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://hsqldb.org/doc/guide/sqlgeneral-chapt.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://hsqldb.org/doc/guide/sqlgeneral-chapt.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13821531" author="davsclaus" created="Wed, 13 Nov 2013 17:05:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for reporting.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
